[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    139[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Why deduplication prefers Preferred Terms (terminology convention)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    140[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Why Neptune bulk loader is faster than individual inserts (performance rationale)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    141[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Why deterministic IDs enable idempotent loads (design decision)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    142[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Why cross-terminology edges are "the heart of normalization" (architectural insight)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Why cache TTL is 24 hours (terminology release cadence)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    144[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Why Redis uses SSL (ElastiCache security)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    145[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - What each UMLS relationship type code means (REL field semantics)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    146[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    147[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The opening disclaimer is well-calibrated: it sets expectations about UMLS complexity (millions of concepts) and positions the code as "a sketch that helps you understand the shape of the solution."
