[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    151[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Logical Flow
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    153[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The code reads top-to-bottom in a pedagogically sound order:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    154[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 1. Configuration and constants (terminology landscape, relationship mappings)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    155[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 2. UMLS file parsing (input, domain-specific format knowledge)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    156[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 3. Neptune bulk load file generation (transformation)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    157[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 4. Neptune bulk load triggering (storage)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    158[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 5. Normalization query service with caching (the primary use case)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 6. Hierarchy traversal for value sets (advanced query pattern)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 7. Batch normalization (pipeline integration)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 8. Full pipeline assembly (putting it together)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 9. Gap to production (honest assessment)
